Titolo: Redline (1999 video game)

Anno: 1999

Descrizione: Redline is a 1999 post-apocalyptic combination first-person shooter/car combat game for Windows. It was developed by Beyond Games and published by Accolade. In Europe, the game is known as Redline - Gang Warfare: 2066. It is a spiritual successor to the Atari Lynx video game BattleWheels. The game was noted for its ability to enter or exit vehicles during combat at anytime; thus, combining the genres of car combat and first-person shooting. This was the last game Accolade published before being acquired by Infogrames.